<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="32" type="note">
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="32">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="32">
Also 
<bibRefCitation author="Cobos, A" journalOrPublisher="Archivos de Instituto de Aclimatacion (Almeria)" pageId="27" pageNumber="44" pagination="103 - 165" refId="B19" refString="Cobos, A, 1956. Ensayo monografico sobre las Anthaxia Eschs. (Coleoptera, Buprestidae) de America. Primera parte: Subgeneros Cylindrophora Sol. y Paracuris Obenb. Archivos de Instituto de Aclimatacion (Almeria) 5: 103 - 165" title="Ensayo monografico sobre las Anthaxia Eschs. (Coleoptera, Buprestidae) de America. Primera parte: Subgeneros Cylindrophora Sol. y Paracuris Obenb." volume="5" year="1956">Cobos (1956)</bibRefCitation>
stressed in his description the strange appearence of this species and attributed it to 
<taxonomicName class="Hexapoda" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="32">Anthaxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with strong doubts. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bílý" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Cobos" baseAuthorityYear="1956" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Sanchezia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bucki">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="32">Sanchezia bucki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Charlesina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mrazi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="32">Charlesina mrazi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are further Neotropical species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Buprestidae</taxonomicName>
mimicking 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="32" phylum="? arthropoda" rank="family">Lycidae</taxonomicName>
. As far as I know, there are only some species of the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Hexapoda" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="32">Agrilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1897" class="Hexapoda" family="Buprestidae" genus="Agrilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dilaticornis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="32">Agrilus dilaticornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kerremans, 1897 species-group) and Chilean species 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Philippi &amp; Philippi" baseAuthorityYear="1860" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Philandia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="valdiviana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="32">Philandia valdiviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Philippi &amp; Philippi, 1860) mimicking Lycid beetles.
</paragraph>
